node.text: I know we’re all handling this differently and being affected, ( effected? idk affected & effected be beating my ass ) by this in ways we couldn't imagine but i just wanted to offer my words in hopes that it resonates with someone. These uncharted waters but the only way i've seen my days get brighter is by holding dear the things I have remaining whether thats friends family or books. And after all of this we should keep that same mindset life is fragile and life is to be cherished, love relentlessly and limitlessly. ❤️

I had the honor of being the keynote speaker at Edsel Ford's Class of 2018 graduation. At age 20 Im not too far from where they are, even though it may seem like it. I give them advice on life, the dangers of comparison, the importance of receiving support and giving it, how fundamental it is to trust in your heart and to follow your dreams. I hope you all hear my words and believe them aswell. Defend your dreams, because they're all we have.

Sincerely, 
Demetrius Harmon

This was going to be one of my favorite events because I love movies, every movie i put up I hand picked, i couldnt wait to see everyone in their own space while sharing a space. Any event ive ever done hasnt been about making money or about myself even, its always been about taking this community we’ve created online and bringing it into the real world, seeing real faces and making real connections and feeling safe to do so as who you really are and anyone who’s ever been to one will vouch for that. Its unfortunate but we’ll figure it out. My favorite part is seeing everyone saying “i wish i was from detroit” because we aint ever been a destination city like new york or LA or even Chicago but ima make sure i continue change that with yall help.❤️. All ticket orders soon to be refunded and hopefully ill have another event for us before the summer ends.

node.text:
Pride month is meant to celebrate and honor a group that has been fighting for equity on a global scale. Sadly, companies tend to use Pride Month as a way to market and pander to the LGBTQ+ community without any real work being done outside of these products or marketing techniques. A few years ago we at You Matter released a rainbow flag that was sold at production cost to show selfless solidarity, and although our intentions were pure, the execution fell short. We’ve spent the time in between learning how we can be better allies and we hope to take a step in the right direction this Pride Month and each one to come. We’ve learned that most times the best way to help is through creating room for those to speak their truth, creating spaces for people to blossom and providing resources in order to contribute to this community striving. We hope to keep learning and growing because we truly believe everyone deserves to be exactly who they want to be, no one should have to hide their sexual orientation or gender identity out of fear. In honor of this year’s Pride Month, You Matter is donating $25,000 to the Ruth Ellis Center in Michigan, whose mission is to create opportunities  LGBTQ+ youth to build their vision of a positive future with the vision of creating a world where LGBTQ+ young people are safe and supported no matter where they go. You Matter will also be donating another $25,000 to individual Gofundme pages to help pay for transitional surgeries for  LGBTQ+ youth who are in need of financial assistance. 

@youmatter
